# Testing

- **Playwright**: Use Playwright for end-to-end testing
- **Vitest**: Use Vitest for unit testing, never use Bun test
- **Test structure**: Place tests in `tests/e2e/` directory
- **Test data**: Use `@faker-js/faker` for generating test data
- **Test scripts**: Use `bun run scripts/add-survey-test-data.ts` for test data

Never use Bun for testing, always use Vitest.
```bash
bun run test:run
```

## Testing patterns

- **E2E tests**: Write comprehensive end-to-end tests
- **Unit tests**: Write unit tests for functions and components
- **Test data generation**: Use Faker.js for realistic test data
- **Test isolation**: Ensure tests are isolated and don't depend on each other
- **Test coverage**: Aim for high test coverage of critical paths
- **Visual testing**: Use Playwright for visual regression testing

## Test structure

```typescript
// E2E test example
import {test, expect} from '@playwright/test';

test('user can create a survey', async ({page}) => {
  await page.goto('/surveys/create');
  await page.fill('[name="title"]', 'Test Survey');
  await page.fill('[name="description"]', 'Test Description');
  await page.click('button[type="submit"]');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\/surveys\/[a-zA-Z0-9-]+/);
  await expect(page.locator('h1')).toContainText('Test Survey');
});
```

```typescript
// Unit test example
import {describe, expect, it} from 'vitest';

describe('survey', () => {
  it('should be created', () => {
    expect(true).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

## Test data generation

```typescript
// Using Faker.js for test data
import {faker} from '@faker-js/faker';

const generateSurveyData = () => ({
  title: faker.lorem.words(3),
  description: faker.lorem.paragraph(),
  campaignTitle: faker.company.name()
});

// Test data script
bun run scripts/add-survey-test-data.ts
```

## Testing best practices

- **Page object model**: Use page objects for test organisation
- **Test hooks**: Use beforeEach/afterEach for test setup/cleanup
- **Assertions**: Use descriptive assertions with clear error messages
- **Test naming**: Use descriptive test names that explain the scenario
- **Performance**: Keep tests fast and efficient
